  "text": "The concept of sustainability has been defined and applied inconsistently in different disciplines. An often quoted definition originates from the World Commission on Environment and Development (1987) -'development that meets the needs of the present without compromising the ability of future generations to meet their needs' [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Rogers 2008, de Brito et al 2008) . However, as noted by [CITATION_3] , such a broad definition is difficult to apply and provides little guidance on how organizations might identify the present and future needs and how to fulfill them, or how to balance the organizational responsibility for multiple stakeholders.",
